# Verible lint rule configuration for QuickUVM-generated SystemVerilog.
# Syntax: one rule per line, `+rule` to enable, `-rule` to disable,
# `+rule=param:value` to configure. Defaults are Verible's standard style set.
# See docs/style_systemverilog.md. After the first CI run, disable any rule
# here (with a one-line rationale) rather than weakening the generated style.

# Enforce the project's 100-column choice (matches the formatter).
+line-length=length:100

# UVM/`uvm_*` macros are not always followed by ';' — keep Verible from
# flagging the macro-call style the templates use.
-uvm-macro-semicolon
